description:
En el corazón de Chichen Itzá, la serpiente emplumada, conocida como Kukulkán, cobra vida al atardecer. Este dios, que combina la majestuosidad de la serpiente y el quetzal, simboliza la unión de la tierra y el cielo. Durante los equinoccios, la sombra proyectada sobre la pirámide da la apariencia de una serpiente descendiendo, mostrando el avanzado conocimiento astronómico de los mayas.
.
In the heart of Chichen Itzá, the feathered serpent, known as Kukulkán, comes to life at sunset. This god, combining the majesty of the serpent and the quetzal bird, symbolizes the union of earth and sky. During the equinoxes, the shadow cast on the pyramid gives the appearance of a descending serpent, showcasing the advanced astronomical knowledge of the Maya.

#ChichenItza #Kukulkan #FeatheredSerpent #MagicalSunset #Equinox #MayaCulture #WorldHeritage #AncientMysteries #TravelMexico

description:
El Chacmool es una figura enigmática y fascinante en la cultura maya, especialmente en Chichen Itzá. Representando una figura masculina reclinada con un cuenco sobre su abdomen, se utilizaba en rituales y sacrificios, actuando como intermediario entre los dioses y los hombres. Su presencia en templos como el de los Guerreros subraya su importancia en ceremonias sagradas, reflejando la sofisticación y espiritualidad de los mayas.

🔹 ¿Sabías que el Chacmool sostenía ofrendas y líquidos sagrados en su cuenco? Un testimonio de la profunda conexión espiritual de los mayas. 🔹

✨ ¡Descubre más sobre esta increíble figura en tu próxima visita a Chichen Itzá! ✨

---------------------------------

The Chacmool is an enigmatic and fascinating figure in Maya culture, especially in Chichen Itzá. Representing a reclining male figure with a bowl on his abdomen, it was used in rituals and sacrifices, acting as an intermediary between the gods and men. Its presence in temples like the Temple of the Warriors highlights its importance in sacred ceremonies, reflecting the sophistication and spirituality of the Maya.

🔹 Did you know that the Chacmool held offerings and sacred liquids in its bowl? A testament to the deep spiritual connection of the Maya. 🔹

✨ Discover more about this incredible figure on your next visit to Chichen Itzá! ✨

description:
UMA DAS 7 MARAVILHAS DO MUNDO ⬇️

Esta é a nossa primeira vez numa das 7 maravilhas do Mundo. Sim, é verdade, Roma é muito mais perto, mas nunca fomos lá 😂

O Chichén Itzá fica na Península de Yucatán e era um dos pontos que queríamos mesmo visitar durante a nossa viagem. 
Como atração turística que é, claro que os preços estão sempre inflacionados. Pagamos cerca de 35€ por pessoa. 
O recinto é muito grande e dentro dele também é possível ver varias ruínas de edificações que faziam parte desta grande cidade Maia, sendo a principal atração o templo de Kukulcán (a pirâmide central).

Que maravilhas do Mundo já visitaste?

One of the 7 Wonders of the World ⬇️

This was our first time visiting one of the 7 Wonders of the World. Yes, it’s true, Rome is much closer, but we’ve never been there 😂

Chichén Itzá is located in the Yucatán Peninsula and was one of the places we really wanted to visit during our trip.
As a tourist attraction, of course, the prices are always inflated. We paid around €35 per person.
The site is very large and within it you can also see several ruins of buildings that were part of this great Mayan city, the main attraction being the Kukulcán temple (the central pyramid).

Which Wonders of the World have you visited?

El Templo de Kukulkán no solo es una maravilla arquitectónica, sino también un reflejo de la precisión matemática de los mayas. ¿Sabías que cada cara de la pirámide tiene 91 escalones, sumando 364, más la plataforma superior que representa el día 365 del año? 🌟
.
The Temple of Kukulkán is not only an architectural marvel but also a reflection of the Mayans' mathematical precision. Did you know that each face of the pyramid has 91 steps, totaling 364, plus the upper platform representing the 365th day of the year? 🌟

#ChichenItza #chichenitzamexico #mexico #ruinas #ruinasmayas #mayanculture #mexicotravel #yucatan #yucatanturismo #travel #reel #travelreel #capcut

¿Qué hay dentro del Templo de Kukulkan? En la década de 1930 se descubrió que dentro de la misma pirámide había otro templo piramidal de menor tamaño donde se encuentra el jaguar de color rojo y con jade en forma de mosaicos.

En el 2015, se descubrió por la UNAM que debajo del Templo había un cenote y que es cubierta por una segunda estructura de 10 metros de altura aproximadamente. 
.
What is inside the Temple of Kukulkan? In the 1930s, it was discovered that within the pyramid itself, there was another smaller pyramid temple where the red jaguar with jade mosaic is located.

In 2015, it was discovered by UNAM that beneath the Temple, there is a cenote covered by a second structure approximately 10 meters tall.

description:
Did you know? The main structure at Chichen Itza, as highlighted by Arqueología Mexicana, features a temple at its top with openings on all four cardinal points. During the equinoxes, sunlight creates seven triangles on its side, symbolizing the god Kukulkan.
.
¿Sabías qué? La estructura principal de Chichen Itza, según Arqueología Mexicana, cuenta con un templo en su cima con vanos en los cuatro puntos cardinales. Durante los equinoccios, la luz solar crea siete triángulos en su costado, simbolizando al dios Kukulkan.

description:
¿Sabías que el Jaguar en la cultura Maya es un símbolo de “poder”? Incluso, lo relacionaban con el inframundo y como símbolo de vida y fertilidad. Era un animal sagrado para toda su civilización.

Cuando visites Chichen Itzá, verás por muchas partes las caras del famoso “Balam” talladas en sus pirámides. ¡Conócelo!
.
Did you know that the Jaguar was considered a symbol of power for the Mayan Civilization? This majestic animal was associated with the underworld and symbolized life and fertility. It held sacred significance throughout their civilization.

When visiting Chichen Itza, you'll encounter depictions of the famous "Balam" carved into its pyramids, representing the jaguar's presence and importance. Come face to face with the jaguar at Chichen Itza!

description:
📍Chichen Itzá , maravilla del mundo moderno 🇲🇽info ⬇️
Ya has visitado esta maravilla del mundo ?🤩
✔️Chichén Itzá es una antigua ciudad maya ubicada en la península de Yucatán, México. Se encuentra en el estado de Yucatán, aproximadamente a 2 horas y media de Cancún y a tan solo 40 kilómetros del Pueblo Mágico de Valladolid.

✔️La zona arqueológica de Chichén Itzá es uno de los destinos imperdibles en México, un sitio turístico que ha sido reconocido como una de las Siete Maravillas del Mundo Moderno debido a su impresionante arquitectura y su profundo significado para la civilización maya.

✔️La mejor opción para llegar a Chichén Itzá, tanto desde Cancún como desde otros puntos de la Riviera Maya, como Playa del Carmen y Tulum, es alquilar un vehículo y llegar por tu cuenta. Esto te dará la libertad de moverte a tu propio ritmo y de llegar temprano para evitar las multitudes o también puedes contratar un tour desde cualquiera de las ciudades cercanas que te ofrecen transporte y todo incluido por un buen precio.
✔️Chichén Itzá generalmente abre al público todos los días de la semana, desde los lunes hasta los domingos, en un horario de 8:00 a.m. a 4:30 p.m. La taquilla abre desde las 8:00 a.m. y cierra a las 4:00 p.m.

✔️Para el año 2024, el precio de entrada para los mexicanos es $285 pesos mexicanos (MXN), y para los viajeros internacionales la tarifa de ingreso es $643 MXN. Los domingos, la entrada es gratuita para los mexicanos.

✔️ Es aconsejable contratar un guía oficial que puedes encontrar a la entrada y que tiene un costo aprox de $1000 pesos mexicanos que puede ser tomado en grupo.

fullName: Photo by Chichen Itza on March 26, 2024.

description:
Chichén Itzá, una joya del patrimonio mundial ubicada en la península de Yucatán, México, es mucho más que un conjunto de antiguas ruinas. Es un testimonio de la grandeza y la sofisticación de la civilización maya, cuyo legado perdura hasta nuestros días.

En el corazón de Chichén Itzá se encuentra la imponente Pirámide de Kukulkán, una maravilla arquitectónica que domina el paisaje circundante. Esta estructura escalonada, dedicada al dios serpiente emplumada Kukulkán, sirve como un monumento a la sabiduría astronómica de los antiguos mayas. Durante los equinoccios de primavera y otoño, las sombras proyectadas por los escalones de la pirámide crean la ilusión de una serpiente que desciende de manera majestuosa, un fenómeno que atrae a visitantes de todo el mundo.

Además de la Pirámide de Kukulkán, Chichén Itzá alberga una impresionante variedad de estructuras arquitectónicas, incluidos el Templo de los Guerreros, el Gran Juego de Pelota y el Observatorio, cada uno testigo de la habilidad y la creatividad de los antiguos constructores mayas.

Pero más allá de su grandeza física, Chichén Itzá es un lugar cargado de significado espiritual y cultural. Cada piedra, cada relieve tallado cuenta una historia de mitos y leyendas, de sacrificios y ofrendas, de la búsqueda de la armonía con el cosmos y la naturaleza.

Hoy en día, Chichén Itzá sigue siendo un destino de peregrinación para aquellos que buscan conectarse con el pasado y maravillarse ante la grandeza de una civilización perdida. Sus ruinas son un recordatorio tangible de la capacidad humana para crear y trascender, un testimonio de que, incluso en el transcurso de los siglos, la belleza y el misterio de Chichén Itzá continúan asombrando e inspirando a todos los que tienen el privilegio de visitar este sitio extraordinario.

Chichén Itzá, Maravilla del Mundo ✨🥰

a must-see among the New 7 Wonders of the World since 2007! 🏛️ 

With over 2.5 million visitors annually, reaching this archaeological gem is a breeze by car, bus, or tour. 🚗🚌

Chichen Itza’s ancient Mayan ruins are divided into Old Chichen and Chichen Itza. You’ll encounter 26 fascinating sites, including the iconic Chichen Itza Pyramid (El Castillo), the mysterious Observatory (El Caracol), and more. 🌿✨

Tickets are USD 41 for adults, USD 15 for Mexican citizens, and free for locals and Mexican residents every Sunday (bring your ID!). 🎟️

For a deeper dive into Mayan culture, hire a guide to walk you through. 📜🧑‍🏫

Chichén Itzá is open daily from 8:00 am to 5:00 pm. ⏰

Take a chance to explore this historical wonderland if you visit Tulum, Playa del Carmen, or Cancun. 🌴🌊

fullName: Photo by Chichen Itza on January 08, 2024.

description:
One of the new 7 wonders of the world - Chichen Itza 🇲🇽

📍Chichen Itza, Yucatan, Mexico 🇲🇽 

Save and share this to visit next time when you’re in Cancún !!

We recently visited this world’s wonder, a UNESCO world heritage site, renowned for it’s iconic pyramid, El Castillo.
It’s a well known archaeological site which welcomes over 2,500,000 visitors each year.

During spring and fall season, thousands of visitors travel to Chichen Itza to watch the shadow of the serpent god Kukulcan travel up and down the pyramid.

It’s also observed that the temple mimics the chirping sound of the quetzal bird when humans clap their hands around it !!

Timings: Monday to Sunday, 8 to 5 PM

It’s hardly 2-3 hours away if you’re staying in Cancún. You can book guided tour and day trip from Cancún to Chichen Itza and witness a testament to Mayan tales and it’s architectural brilliance !!

fullName: Photo by Chichen Itza on August 11, 2023.

description:
Did you know that Chichen Itza is not only a renowned archaeological site but also one of the “New 7 Wonders of the World”? This prestigious title was bestowed upon Chichen Itza due to its large concentration of culturally-significant, ancient manmade wonders and its placement in the top 7 of all nominees during international voting.

Nestled in the lush landscapes of Mexico’s Yucatan Peninsula, this ancient Mayan city stands as a testament to the ingenuity and brilliance of the Mayan civilization, dating back to the pre-Columbian era. Designated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, Chichen Itza holds a treasure trove of historical and cultural significance.

One of the most iconic structures at Chichen Itza is the impressive step pyramid known as El Castillo, or the Temple of Kukulkan. This architectural masterpiece is not only awe-inspiring but also serves as an astronomical marvel. During the equinoxes in March and September, a remarkable event occurs where the play of sunlight and shadows on the pyramid creates an illusion of a serpent slithering down the stairs. This phenomenon is a testament to the advanced knowledge of the Mayans in astronomy and their ability to incorporate celestial alignments into their monumental structures.

The city of Chichen Itza was once a thriving hub of commerce, religion, and political power for the Mayan people. Its strategic location enabled it to flourish as a center of trade, connecting different regions of the Yucatan Peninsula. The site features various architectural wonders, including the Great Ball Court, which is one of the largest and best-preserved ball courts in Mesoamerica. It is believed that ball games played here held significant religious and ceremonial importance for the Mayans.

Apart from its grand structures, Chichen Itza also houses the Sacred Cenote, a natural sinkhole considered sacred by the Mayans. Archaeologists have uncovered numerous offerings, including precious artifacts and human remains, providing valuable insights into the religious practices of the ancient civilization.

Have you been to any of the New 7 Wonders of the World? Share your experiences in the comments and let’s inspire each other.

description:
Chichen Itza's Kukulkan Nights, also known as the Light & Sound Show, is available from Friday to Sunday and it showcases a video mapping of the Mayan history and culture. It's a magical way to witness the night sky.✨🌙💫

Las Noches de Kukulkán de Chichén Itzá, también conocidas como Espectáculo de Luz y Sonido, están disponibles de viernes a domingo y muestran un video mapping de la historia y cultura maya. Es una forma mágica de contemplar el cielo nocturno.✨🌙💫

description:
In 1997, radar studies led to the discovery of a hidden cenote under the pyramid of El Castillo de Chichén Itzá!
A recent investigation led people to believe that this cenote was kept hidden because it represented the center of the world. 🌎 What are your thoughts?
-
En 1997, los estudios de radar permitieron descubrir un cenote oculto bajo la pirámide de El Castillo de Chichén Itzá!
Una investigación reciente hizo creer que este cenote se mantenía oculto porque representaba el centro del mundo. 🌎 ¿Tú qué opinas?

description:
Do you know what is celebrated on the 5th of May?
The famous Cinco de Mayo commemorates the anniversary of Mexico's victory over the Second French Empire at the Battle of Puebla in 1862, led by General Ignacio Zaragoza! 🇲🇽🇲🇽
-
¿Sabes qué se celebra el 5 de mayo?
El famoso Cinco de Mayo conmemora el aniversario de la victoria de México sobre el Segundo Imperio Francés en la Batalla de Puebla de 1862, dirigida por el general Ignacio Zaragoza. 🇲🇽🇲🇽

description:
Welcome to the #mayanruins of the Yucatan peninsula in #mexico🇲🇽! The mayan civilization existed in this part of mexico 🇲🇽 from 250 AD to 900 AD. Situated only 3 hours away from Cancun or Playa del Carmen you can visit Chichen itza , one of the 7 wonder's of the world! 

If you are looking to get away from the beaches and learn about some #mexicanhistory or see some beautiful ruins then Chichen itza is for you.

DM me to learn more about the mayan ruins :)

 #chichenitza #tulum #playadelcarmen #valladolidmexico #izamal #yucatan #yucatanpeninsula #cancun #cancuntours #mayantours #mayans  #koshermexico #koshertravel #history #photography #travelphotgraphy #travelgram #sevenwondersoftheworld

description:
It's April 18, and we celebrate World Heritage Day! A day dedicated to promoting awareness and appreciation for cultural heritage and the importance of preserving it for future generations. Read more as we talk about it on our blog (link in bio) 🌏🌎🌍
UNESCO en español  @unesco 
UNESCO @unesco_es 
-
Es 18 de abril y celebramos el Día Mundial del Patrimonio. Un día dedicado a promover la concienciación y el aprecio por el patrimonio cultural y la importancia de preservarlo para las generaciones futuras. Más información al respecto en nuestro blog (link en la biografía)🌏🌎🌍

description:
"Unlock the Mystery and Adventure of Chichen Itza: Marvel at the Mighty Pyramids and Experience the Wonders of Ancient Mayan Civilization!"

Chichen Itza is a world-renowned archaeological site located in the Yucatan Peninsula of Mexico, and it is undoubtedly one of the most fascinating and awe-inspiring destinations in the world. As you explore the site, you'll be transported back in time to a world of mystery and adventure, where the mighty pyramids, ancient temples, and towering observatory reveal the secrets of the long-lost Mayan civilization.

description:
Discover the ancient wonder of Chichen Itza! Behold the awe-inspiring Pyramid of Kukulkan rising majestically in the distance amidst a lush jungle landscape. Walk in the footsteps of the Mayan civilization and immerse yourself in their rich history and culture. Don't miss your chance to witness one of the most iconic archaeological sites in the world. Visit Chichen Itza and let its grandeur leave you breathless.
-
Descubre la antigua maravilla de Chichén Itzá. Contempla la imponente Pirámide de Kukulkán que se alza majestuosa en la distancia en medio de un exuberante paisaje selvático. Siga los pasos de la civilización maya y sumérjase en su rica historia y cultura. No pierda la oportunidad de presenciar uno de los yacimientos arqueológicos más emblemáticos del mundo. Visite Chichén Itzá y deje que su grandeza le deje sin aliento.

description:
La pirámide de Kukulkán en Chichén Itzá es una de las atracciones turísticas más populares de México. Este lugar declarado Patrimonio de la Humanidad por la UNESCO es una de las Siete Maravillas del Mundo por una razón: sus imponentes pirámides y templos son sencillamente impresionantes. La vista a la pirámide principal, El Castillo, es para disfrutar de una vista impresionante de todo el sitio.
-
The Kukulkan pyramid at Chichen Itza is one of the most popular tourist attractions in Mexico. This UNESCO World Heritage site is one of the Seven Wonders of the World for a reason – its imposing pyramids and temples are simply breathtaking. The top of the main pyramid, El Castillo, gives you a stunning view of the entire site.
#ChichenItza

fullName: Photo by Chichen Itza on February 28, 2023.

description:
¿Sabías qué... Chichén Itzá debe su nombre a un cenote cercano?
La península de Yucatán está llena de cenotes naturales. En el extremo norte del yacimiento arqueológico hay un gran cenote, también llamado Cenote Sagrado, que se cree que se utilizaba para sacrificios. Chichén significa "boca de los pozos" e Itzá hace referencia a la tribu maya que habitaba estas regiones.
-
Did you know... Chichen Itza gets its name from a cenote nearby?
The Yucatan peninsula is full of natural cenotes. A large cenote also called the Sacred Cenote and believed to have been used for sacrificial purposes is seen at the northern end of the archaeological site. Chichen means “mouth of the wells” and Itza refers to the Mayan tribe that lived in these regions.
#ChichenItza

description:
Chichen Itza Facts: At the Thousand Columns of Chichen Itza, when counting the columns, we’ll only be able to count 200 in total. The actual name of “The Thousand Columns” comes from the greatness it inspires. In reality, this used to be another temple that connected with the Temple of the Warriors 😱

Datos de Chichen Itza: En las Mil Columnas de Chichen Itza, al contar las columnas, solo encontramos 200 en total. El nombre de “Las Mil Columnas” viene de la grandeza que inspiran. En realidad, esta solía ser otro templo que se conectaba con el Templo de los Guerreros.

Photo credits: @carloshdzsuarez

description:
Chichen Itza Facts: The number of stairs of the Pyramid of Kukulkan is 91 on each side, meaning a total of 364. By adding the platform, the last step that holds the temple at the top of the pyramid, it's a total of 365 steps, just like the 365 days of the year! 🤯

Datos de Chichén Itzá: El número de escalones de la Pirámide de Kukulkán es de 91 de cada lado, indicando un total de 364. Al sumar la plataforma, el último escalón que sostiene el templo superior, da un total de 365 escalones, igual que los 365 días del año! 🤯

 
Photo credits: @carloshdzsuarez

A recent investigation led people to believe that this cenote was kept hidden because it represented the center of the world. 🌎

fullName: Photo by Chichen Itza on November 08, 2022.

description:
Hanal Pixan is the name for the festivities which take place in the Yucatan which are similar to the Day of the Dead celebrations throughout Mexico. 
It is a special event for the relatives of the deceased because they know that during these days, from October 31 to November 2, the souls "receive permission" to visit their relatives...

If you want to learn more about this date, check out our blog:
https://www.chichenitza.com/blog/hanal-pixan-the-day-of-the-death

fullName: Photo by Chichen Itza on November 01, 2022.

description:
Did you know that the City of Chichen Itzá was once bought by Edward Herbert Thompson? 🧐
-
It was at the beginning of the 20th Century when Thompson begun a research at the site and purchased the site.
By 1926, the Mexican government expropriated the land and sued Thompson, accusing him of having illegally appropriated the property. 😮

description:
Year 1924. The Governor of Yucatan, José María "Xanoc" Iturralde Traconis with a group of people and their bodyguards, pose for a photograph next to the Kukulkan temple in the archaeological zone of Chichen Itza, Yucatan. The popular nickname of Xanoc that the governor carried during his lifetime, was supposedly given to him because of the great affection he had for the small town that is located south of Valladolid and that bears that name, and that in Mayan means shark. #ChichenItza #Yucatan #Mexico

fullName: Photo by Chichen Itza in Chichén-Itzá, Yucatan, Mexico.

description:
The descent of Kukulkan.

As in every equinox when the Sun is over the Equator and the day lasts the same as the night, the shadow of the plumed serpent appears on the western alfarda of the north stairway, shortly before sunset. It is made up of seven inverted triangles of light that seem to descend and join at the base of the staircase with the stone head of the Kukulkan serpent. #ChichenItza #Yucatan #Mexico

fullName: Photo by Chichen Itza in Chichén-Itzá, Yucatan, Mexico.

description:
Year 1932. A group of hunters, including men and children, passing through the archaeological zone of Chichen Itza. They are accompanied by their dogs, which played an important role during the hunt. The so-called "Batida" is a form of subsistence hunting in which a group of people from the community participate, to obtain deer or wild boar meat, it has not changed much over the years. In this modality, the hunters (the bidders) participate, in charge of chasing the prey, while the other group (the shooters) await the arrival of the potential prey. Pic by @yucatanpasadoglorioso #chichenitza #Yucatan #Mexico

description:
¡Feliz día de Muertos!💐
Hoy en México celebramos una de nuestras más preciadas tradiciones. Honramos a los que han partido a través de ofrendas, colocando sus fotografías, platillos favoritos, y decoramos los altares con muchos colores; iluminamos su camino con veladoras y esperamos su llegada💐

En Yucatán no puede faltar el pib o mucbipollo, si estás de visita por la zona, ¡no dudes en probarlo!
.
.

description:
“The city of the water sorcerers”

Chichen Itza is one of the main archaeological sites on the Yucatan Peninsula, in Mexico. It was and is a sacred city and Mayan pilgrimage center founded by the Itza, the so-called water sorcerers, in the 5th century AD.

The Mayans developed one of the most fascinating and enigmatic cultures of Humanity in the heart of the dense jungles of Chiapas, Guatemala, Yucatán, Honduras and Belize. Although the habitat in which they settled was not very favorable for urban development, they achieved great splendor.

description:
According to research, the Mayans tattooed symbols on their bodies. The inhabitants made tattoos for different reasons, they gave them a meaning by impregnating engravings of gods and warriors on their skin because they had the thought that the deities were going to take care of them. Through this modifying technique they showed their respect towards them, they believed that this way they would have peace and obtain prosperity. The tattoos showed his devotion. Pic by @madskristensenofficial #ChichenItza #Yucatan #Mexico
